# 2. Full TCP Port Scan

## Objective

Discover every TCP port on the target.

## Command

```bash
nmap -p- <TARGET-IP>
```

## Output File

```bash
nmap -p- <TARGET-IP> -oN raw-output/full-port-scan.txt
```

## Explanation

- `-p-` scans all **65,535 TCP ports**.
- Used to identify every open TCP service.

